msgctxt "mn84:7.9"
msgid "idhassa brāhmaṇo, idhassa vesso, idhassa suddo pāṇātipātā paṭivirato adinnādānā paṭivirato … pe … sammādiṭṭhi kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjeyya no vā? "
msgstr "Take a brahmin, merchant, or worker who doesn’t kill living creatures, steal, or commit sexual misconduct. They don’t use speech that’s false, divisive, harsh, or nonsensical. And they’re contented, kind-hearted, with right view. When their body breaks up, after death, would they be reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm, or not? "

msgctxt "mn84:7.10"
msgid "Kathaṃ vā te ettha hotī”ti? "
msgstr "Or how do you see this?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn84:7.11"
msgid "“Suddopi hi, bho kaccāna, pāṇātipātā paṭivirato, adinnādānā paṭivirato … pe … sammādiṭṭhi kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjeyya. "
msgstr "“Such a brahmin, merchant, or worker would be reborn in a good place. "

msgctxt "mn84:7.12"
msgid "Evaṃ me ettha hoti, evañca pana me etaṃ arahataṃ sutan”ti. "
msgstr "That’s what I think, but I’ve also heard it from the perfected ones.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.88, sc12
msgctxt "mn84:7.13"
msgid "“Sādhu sādhu, mahārāja. "
msgstr "“Good, good, great king! "

msgctxt "mn84:7.14"
msgid "Sādhu kho te etaṃ, mahārāja, evaṃ hoti, sādhu ca pana te etaṃ arahataṃ sutaṃ. "
msgstr "It’s good that you think so, and it’s good that you’ve heard it from the perfected ones. "

msgctxt "mn84:7.15"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, mahārāja, "
msgstr "What do you think, great king? "

msgctxt "mn84:7.16"
msgid "yadi evaṃ sante, ime cattāro vaṇṇā samasamā honti no vā? "
msgstr "If this is so, are the four castes equal or not? "

msgctxt "mn84:7.17"
msgid "Kathaṃ vā te ettha hotī”ti? "
msgstr "Or how do you see this?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn84:7.18"
msgid "“Addhā kho, bho kaccāna, evaṃ sante, ime cattāro vaṇṇā samasamā honti. "
msgstr "“Certainly, Master Kaccāna, in this case these four castes are equal. "

msgctxt "mn84:7.19"
msgid "Nesaṃ ettha kiñci nānākaraṇaṃ samanupassāmī”ti. "
msgstr "I can’t see any difference between them.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn84:7.20"
msgid "“Imināpi kho etaṃ, mahārāja, pariyāyena veditabbaṃ yathā ghosoyeveso lokasmiṃ: "
msgstr "“And here’s another way to understand that the claims of the brahmins are just propaganda. "

msgctxt "mn84:7.21"
msgid "‘brāhmaṇova seṭṭho vaṇṇo, hīno añño vaṇṇo … pe … brahmadāyādā’”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya8, sc13
msgctxt "mn84:8.1"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, mahārāja, "
msgstr "What do you think, great king? "

msgctxt "mn84:8.2"
msgid "idha khattiyo sandhiṃ vā chindeyya, nillopaṃ vā hareyya, ekāgārikaṃ vā kareyya, paripanthe vā tiṭṭheyya, paradāraṃ vā gaccheyya, tañce te purisā gahetvā dasseyyuṃ: "
msgstr "Take an aristocrat who breaks into houses, plunders wealth, steals from isolated buildings, commits highway robbery, and commits adultery. Suppose your men arrest him and present him to you, saying: "

msgctxt "mn84:8.3"
msgid "‘ayaṃ te, deva, coro āgucārī. "
msgstr "‘Your Majesty, this man is a bandit, a criminal. "

msgctxt "mn84:8.4"
msgid "Imassa yaṃ icchasi taṃ daṇḍaṃ paṇehī’ti. "
msgstr "Punish him as you will.’ "

msgctxt "mn84:8.5"
msgid "Kinti naṃ kareyyāsī”ti? "
msgstr "What would you do to him?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn84:8.6"
msgid "“Ghāteyyāma vā, bho kaccāna, jāpeyyāma vā pabbājeyyāma vā yathāpaccayaṃ vā kareyyāma. "
msgstr "“I would have him executed, fined, or banished, or dealt with as befits the crime. "

msgctxt "mn84:8.7"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

#. VAR: saṅkhyaṃ → saṅkhaṃ (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "mn84:8.8"
msgid "Yā hissa, bho kaccāna, pubbe ‘khattiyo’ti samaññā sāssa antarahitā; corotveva saṅkhyaṃ gacchatī”ti. "
msgstr "Because he’s lost his former status as an aristocrat, and is just reckoned as a bandit.” "

