msgctxt "mn84:9.18"
msgid "“Imināpi kho etaṃ, mahārāja, pariyāyena veditabbaṃ yathā ghosoyeveso lokasmiṃ: "
msgstr "“This is another way to understand that this is just propaganda: "

msgctxt "mn84:9.19"
msgid "‘brāhmaṇova seṭṭho vaṇṇo, hīno añño vaṇṇo; "
msgstr "‘Only brahmins are the highest caste; other castes are inferior. "

msgctxt "mn84:9.20"
msgid "brāhmaṇova sukko vaṇṇo, kaṇho añño vaṇṇo; "
msgstr "Only brahmins are the light caste; other castes are dark. "

msgctxt "mn84:9.21"
msgid "brāhmaṇāva sujjhanti, no abrāhmaṇā; "
msgstr "Only brahmins are purified, not others. "

msgctxt "mn84:9.22"
msgid "brāhmaṇāva brahmuno puttā orasā mukhato jātā brahmajā brahmanimmitā brahmadāyādā’”ti. "
msgstr "Only brahmins are Brahmā’s rightful sons, born of his mouth, born of Brahmā, created by Brahmā, heirs of Brahmā.’” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya10, pts-vp-pli2.90, sc19
msgctxt "mn84:10.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, rājā mādhuro avantiputto āyasmantaṃ mahākaccānaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When he had spoken, King Avantiputta of Madhurā said to Mahākaccāna, "

msgctxt "mn84:10.2"
msgid "“abhikkantaṃ, bho kaccāna, abhikkantaṃ, bho kaccāna. "
msgstr "“Excellent, Master Kaccāna! Excellent! "

msgctxt "mn84:10.3"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bho kaccāna, nikkujjitaṃ vā ukkujjeyya, paṭicchannaṃ vā vivareyya, mūḷhassa vā maggaṃ ācikkheyya, andhakāre vā telapajjotaṃ dhāreyya ‘cakkhumanto rūpāni dakkhantī’ti; evamevaṃ bhotā kaccānena anekapariyāyena dhammo pakāsito. "
msgstr "As if he were righting the overturned, or revealing the hidden, or pointing out the path to the lost, or lighting a lamp in the dark so people with good eyes can see what’s there, Master Kaccāna has made the teaching clear in many ways. "

msgctxt "mn84:10.4"
msgid "Esāhaṃ bhavantaṃ kaccānaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāmi dhammañca bhikkhusaṃghañca. "
msgstr "I go for refuge to Master Kaccāna, to the teaching, and to the mendicant Saṅgha. "

msgctxt "mn84:10.5"
msgid "Upāsakaṃ maṃ bhavaṃ kaccāno dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti. "
msgstr "From this day forth, may Master Kaccāna remember me as a lay follower who has gone for refuge for life.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn84:10.6"
msgid "“Mā kho maṃ tvaṃ, mahārāja, saraṇaṃ agamāsi. "
msgstr "“Great king, don’t go for refuge to me. "

#. VAR: Tameva tvaṃ → tametaṃ tvaṃ (s1-3, km) | tametaṃ (mr)
msgctxt "mn84:10.7"
msgid "Tameva tvaṃ bhagavantaṃ saraṇaṃ gaccha yamahaṃ saraṇaṃ gato”ti. "
msgstr "You should go for refuge to that same Blessed One to whom I have gone for refuge.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn84:10.8"
msgid "“Kahaṃ pana, bho kaccāna, etarahi so bhagavā viharati arahaṃ sammāsambuddho”ti? "
msgstr "“But where is that Blessed One at present, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn84:10.9"
msgid "“Parinibbuto kho, mahārāja, etarahi so bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho”ti. "
msgstr "“Great king, the Buddha has already become fully extinguished.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya11
msgctxt "mn84:11.1"
msgid "“Sacepi mayaṃ, bho kaccāna, suṇeyyāma taṃ bhagavantaṃ dasasu yojanesu, dasapi mayaṃ yojanāni gaccheyyāma taṃ bhagavantaṃ dassanāya arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ. "
msgstr "“Master Kaccāna, if I heard that the Buddha was within ten leagues, or twenty, or even up to a hundred leagues away, I’d go a hundred leagues to see him. "

msgctxt "mn84:11.2"
msgid "Sacepi mayaṃ, bho kaccāna, suṇeyyāma taṃ bhagavantaṃ vīsatiyā yojanesu, tiṃsāya yojanesu, cattārīsāya yojanesu, paññāsāya yojanesu, paññāsampi mayaṃ yojanāni gaccheyyāma taṃ bhagavantaṃ dassanāya arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn84:11.3"
msgid "Yojanasate cepi mayaṃ bho kaccāna, suṇeyyāma taṃ bhagavantaṃ, yojanasatampi mayaṃ gaccheyyāma taṃ bhagavantaṃ dassanāya arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn84:11.4"
msgid "Yato ca, bho kaccāna, parinibbuto so bhagavā, parinibbutampi mayaṃ bhagavantaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāma dhammañca bhikkhusaṃghañca. "
msgstr "But since the Buddha has become fully extinguished, I go for refuge to that fully extinguished Buddha, to the teaching, and to the Saṅgha. "

msgctxt "mn84:11.5"
msgid "Upāsakaṃ maṃ bhavaṃ kaccāno dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti. "
msgstr "From this day forth, may Master Kaccāna remember me as a lay follower who has gone for refuge for life.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "mn84:11.6"
msgid "Madhurasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ catutthaṃ. "
msgstr ""

